<br>
For myself, I don't use the epic pet a lot. That said, every now and then I am so grateful to have a Bober ont a stick ready. While the Epic may not be able to deal damage like the water, and only tanks just as well as the air, it can do any of these if you need it.<br>
<br>
Sometimes our group tank will die, or the cleric (rather common in PoP where the difference between success and failure in pickup groups can be slim). At such a time if the pet starts playing tank for a residual mob, I click it and get ready to /pet get lost. Its no substitute for a real tank, but if your real tank is down and you have a slowed mob with say a shaman and some casters to look after it, it sure helps.<br>
<br>
I am finding other residual uses for it as well. For instance, if I die and we are doing a CR, I can &quot;store&quot; mana thropugh the rez by getting an Orb up before I am ressurected, and reclaiming the pet on that Orb once rezzed. During the progression of the group, if I accidentally have a pet die (by enrage for example) I can hit the click, grab a solid mana-free pet for the rest of the fight (clicking legs for haste) and then reclaim it at the end of the fight and make a new permanent Water pet without paying a big mana cost. <br>
<br>
Next time the group has any significant downtime, I &quot;charge&quot; the Orb with another pet.<br>
<br>
There are a lot of little uses like this for the Orb aside form its natural stats. Sure, in its own right each one isn't very significant, but added together they make the having of the Epic definetly worthwhile, even if the pet is no longer your mainstay. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=variathemage>Varia the mage</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 61<br> <font color=#333333>(11/14/02 12:06:39 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowergeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=7852.topic&index=11>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: To complete, or not to complete?</span><hr size=1> Go for it.  In addition to the nice stats and a pet who's use is dying off but is still sometimes useful, it looks darn cool!  I liked how the mage epic looked more than the other caster ones back when the first screenshots were leaked and nobody knew which one was for each class.  Maybe I'm strange, but fashion has to count for at least a little. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   It would be a shame not to complete it now than you are so close.<br>
